==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: spread-eagle
<hw>spread"-ea`gle</hw> <pr>(spr⟦ecr⟧d"⟦emac⟧`g'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Characterized by a pretentious, boastful, exaggerated style;
defiantly or extravagantly bombastic, especially regarding of the
greatness of the U. S.; <as>as, a <ex>spread-eagle</ex> orator; a
<ex>spread-eagle</ex> speech</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq. &
Humorous]</mark> <au>[MW10]</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>spread-eagle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: spread-eagle
<hw>spread"-ea`gle</hw> <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To assume a spread-eagled
position; -- it may be done reclining, for relaxation, or momentarily,
as an exhibitionary maneuver in a sport.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>spread-eagled</ent>⟦br⟧
